Privacy Policy
The Privacy Policy was updated on
November 17, 2023
Why should you read this?
You should read this policy carefully because it is a legal document that governs your use of VOLA. We have made this contract easy for you to read, free of legal jargon. Plus, we care about your privacy and pledge to practice what we say in this policy.
What does this privacy policy cover?
This policy covers how Vola. treats personal information that Vola collects and receives. This policy does not apply to the practices of companies that Vola does not own or control (such as Apple, Inc., the Apple iTunes Store, or Facebook) or to people that Vola does not employ or manage.
Personally-Identifiable Information
Personally-Identifiable Information (PII) is data that could potentially identify a specific individual.
Depending on the services you choose, we may collect your PII from a third party that helps us verify your identity and bank account details, including, but not limited to, a copy of your government-issued photo ID or a bank statement. We may also obtain information about you from the financial institution providing your bank account.
